AB  - Climate change threatens the established image and quality of life, carries risks for the real estate market, the construction industry, development projects, the existing real estate fund, as well as the economy. Despite the nature and scale of climate challenges, there are very few studies in Russia analyzing the economic effects of increasing the sustainability of buildings and cities. The authors of this particular study investigated the reasons for the current attitude to the problem and the expediency of investments in the field of improving the energy efficiency of modern buildings and capital repairs of the existing real estate fund. While preparing the material, the authors used a logical analysis of the Russian regulatory framework, methods for improving the energy efficiency of buildings in foreign countries; an economic analysis of the impact of improving the energy efficiency of buildings on the economics of projects, the construction industry, the Russian real estate market. The results of the study are that buildings with higher energy efficiency characteristics: they have greater resistance to current and predicted climate changes by experts. They also provide a higher quality of life and working environment; saving the consumed resources. They demonstrate a longer service life (while other things being equal) and a greater potential for cost growth over time. Each 1USD million investments in the field of energy efficiency improvement of new buildings and existing real estate fund leads to the creation of 13 to 15 new workplaces. This is the highest figure in comparison with other industries. The authors conclude that improving the energy efficiency of buildings is a necessary measure to increase the resilience of the real estate fund, Russian cities to climate risks and at the same time it is a guarantee of maintaining the competitiveness of Russian companies, the construction industry, the real estate market and the economy as a whole. © 2023