AB  - The principal purpose of the current study is to provide building retrofitting methods in order to maximize the stored energy and minimize the dedicated budget for an initial investment as decision parameters. Also, the effects of using the proposed technology in heating and cooling the house, and costs have been evaluated. The optimization process has been used in order to create an optimal configuration of the recommended retrofit values in different cities of Spain, such as Malaga, Cordoba, Valencia, and Madrid. For solving the optimization issue a multi-objective CSO (chameleon swarm optimization) algorithm is employed. Reducing electricity consumption by replacing lighting features and refrigerator models, using insulating materials in exterior walls and windows to increase the U-values, using heat pumps for heating and cooling the building environment, using photovoltaics panels for personal use, including various measures that have been assumed for energy efficiency in the building. Various limitations that affect the cost are related to the volume of adherence to cooling and heating requirements, achieving demand, non-negative limitations related to parameters, and physical limitations of the building environment. Optimum replacements of retrofitting, calculation of saved energy, and budget for retrofitting are proposed. The payback period obtained from the solutions is an average of 3.75-year periods for Malaga, 3.52-year periods for Cordoba, 3.42-year periods for Valencia, and 2-year periods for Madrid. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG. 2023.
