AB  - The paper presents the analysis results of the concept of integrated, “sustainable” development of the area of the old airport complex in the city of Rostov-on-Don. The accounting of the predictive level of energy resources consumption of a conditional site on the territory of the airport renovation at the maximum and minimum density of its development with high, medium, and low-rise buildings is performed. The change in the energy load on utility networks from the real estate objects planned for construction, depending on the level of their energy efficiency, is calculated. Measures are proposed to reduce the energy intensity of buildings based on the application of the European practice in this area. Using the example of calculating the energy load of a conditional area of the renovation, the value of possible savings of energy resources in the amount of 78.5% was obtained, depending on the accepted model of building density. © 2023, The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG.
